# ─── DENY-LIST — credentials, secrets, snapshots ────────────────────────
#
# This repo is PUBLIC. Belt-and-suspenders against accidental commits of any
# credential content. If you find yourself editing this file to allow
# something through, stop and think — almost certainly the right move is to
# rename the file, not loosen the gitignore.
#
# Anything matching a pattern below cannot accidentally be `git add`'d
# unless you pass --force, which gives you one last chance to notice.

# Encrypted vault snapshots (should never be in the repo — they live in iCloud)
*.age

# Anything that looks like a Google service-account or OAuth JSON
*.json
!package.json
!package-lock.json
!tsconfig*.json

# .env files of every flavor
.env
.env.*
*.env

# Private keys / certs in every common form
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
*_rsa
*_rsa.pub
*_ed25519
*_ed25519.pub
id_rsa*
id_ed25519*

# Anything with "secret", "passphrase", "token", "credential" in the name
*secret*
*passphrase*
*token*
*credential*
!CREDENTIAL_VAULT.md
!credential_vault.md
!README.md

# Per-laptop / per-governor state files (never commit)
MANIFEST.txt.canonical
MANIFEST.local.txt
.credential_vault_*
*onboarding_progress*

# Editor / OS noise
*.bak
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
